<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='537343' id='t-537343'>Now, the sun in this poem,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='539696' id='t-539696'>in Wallace Stevens' poem, seems so grave</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='542185' id='t-542185'>because the person in the poem is so afraid.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='545656' id='t-545656'>The sun comes up in the morning through branches,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='548143' id='t-548143'>dispels the dew, the eyes, on the grass,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='551082' id='t-551082'>and defeats stars envisioned as armies.</span>
