<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='558700' id='t-558700'>This sun is not afraid to show his face.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='562040' id='t-562040'>But the person in the poem is afraid.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='565392' id='t-565392'>He might have been up all night.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='566931' id='t-566931'>That is the reveal Stevens
saves for that fourth stanza,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='570913' id='t-570913'>where run away has become a refrain.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='573691' id='t-573691'>This person might want to run away too,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='575883' id='t-575883'>but fortified by the sun's example,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='578173' id='t-578173'>he might just rise.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='580898' id='t-580898'>Stevens saves that sonically odd word &quot;meditation&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='585176' id='t-585176'>for the end.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='586850' id='t-586850'>Unlike the sun, human beings think.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='589751' id='t-589751'>We meditate on past and future, life and death,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='593848' id='t-593848'>above and below.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='596394' id='t-596394'>And it can make us afraid.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
10:11
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='600178' id='t-600178'>Poems, the patterns in poems,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='602248' id='t-602248'>show us not just what somebody thought</span>
